  "prompt": "How can I import contacts from basic mobile to smartphone?",
  "response": "To import contacts from a basic mobile phone to a smartphone, you can try these methods:\n\n1. SIM Card Transfer\n- Insert the SIM card from your basic phone into the smartphone\n- Use the smartphone's contact import/copy feature\n- Select contacts to transfer from SIM card to phone memory\n\n2. Bluetooth Transfer\n- Enable Bluetooth on both phones\n- Pair the devices\n- Send contacts via Bluetooth one by one or in a group\n\n3. Google/Cloud Sync\n- If your basic phone supports Gmail/Google Contacts\n- Sync contacts to Google account\n- Log into same account on new smartphone\n- Contacts will automatically sync\n\n4. Manual Entry\n- Write down contacts\n- Manually enter them into new smartphone\n- Time-consuming but accurate\n\n5. Third-Party Apps\n- Use apps like:\n  - My Contacts Backup\n  - Contact Transfer\n  - Mobile Transfer\n- These apps can help transfer contacts between different phone types\n\n6. Export to CSV\n- If your basic phone allows exporting contacts to CSV file\n- Transfer file to computer\n- Import CSV to new smartphone\n\nThe best method depends on your specific phones and available features. Check your phone's user manual for precise instructions.",
